uk.ac.ebi.gxa.loader.cache
Class AtlasLoadCacheRegistry

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.ebi.gxa.loader.cache.AtlasLoadCacheRegistry

public class AtlasLoadCacheRegistry
extends Object

A singleton registry of AtlasLoadCache objects, indexed by MAGETABInvestigation. This lets handlers in different threads do a lookup on the cache to store objects in, and they only need to specifically know about the MAGETABInvestigation.

Author:
Tony Burdett

registerExperiment

public void registerExperiment(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABInvestigation investigation,
                               AtlasLoadCache cache)
Register an AtlasLoadCache, keyed by investigation, to this registry. Any objects created from this investigation should be placed into this cache.

Note that an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown if the investigation supplied is already associated with a cache in this registry. If you want to replace a cache, use the replaceExperiment(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABInvestigation, AtlasLoadCache) method, or you can deregisterExperiment(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABInvestigation) and then register. Alternatively you can merge objects in a new cache into the one previously registered by calling mergeExperiments(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABInvestigation, AtlasLoadCache).

Parameters:
investigation - the investigation being used to create objects for the cache
cache - the cache holding objects created from this investigation

Register an AtlasLoadCache, keyed by array design, to this registry. Any objects created from this array design should be placed into this cache.

Note that an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown if the array design supplied is already associated with a cache in this registry. If you want to replace a cache, use the replaceArrayDesign(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABArrayDesign, AtlasLoadCache) method, or you can deregisterArrayDesign(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABArrayDesign) and then register. Alternatively you can merge objects in a new cache into the one previously registered by calling mergeArrayDesigns(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABArrayDesign, AtlasLoadCache).

Parameters:
arrayDesign - the array design being used to create objects for the cache
cache - the cache holding objects created from this investigation

public void replaceExperiment(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABInvestigation investigation,

Replace the AtlasLoadCache that is currently registered to the given MAGETABInvestigation with the new one supplied. This is equivalent to calling deregisterExperiment(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABInvestigation) followed by registerExperiment(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABInvestigation, AtlasLoadCache) }

Parameters:
investigation - the investigation keying the cache to replace
cache - the new cache that will replace the current cache
